<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#ffffff"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000080"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rained out</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have a petition to verant about the rain in the game...  i have been watching the times that it rains and on the average it rains once per hour in each zone...<BR>now i know some zones like the swamps should be like this but others like nro or the karanas or even the overthere should get less...  <BR>time in everquest does go at an accelerated pace compaired to real world time but how many times does it rain per month in most places? a few in some, none in others, and all the time in yet others...  now i have heard that 3 hours in real life is about a day in everquest, that means that it rains 3 times each day on the average? open up the flood gates... where is that ark?<BR>come on fix the rain issue so that its at least reasonable... put some randomness in... but dont leave the rain on auto timer</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Goshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Have your favorite druid turn off the rain  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Daemonn1</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Believe it or not - rain is not as bad as it once was.  There was a time (about 8 or 10 months ago) when they changed it.  It is really a lot better now.<P>I don't relly think the rain adds anything to the game.  I would be happy with clear skys at all times.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vizion</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">In beta the rain was an awesome effect the first time you saw it.  I loved battling in the rain with lightning going off, spells going off, etc., but it was also not as frigging foggy as it is now.  The rain would be much more tolerable if they didn't feel the need to nerf your visual range everytime it rained.  C'mon, I can see miles away sometimes when it rains.  The only time it should fog up is in the "winter" months; or even better yet, have it snow in most areas during winter EQ months.  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">  The snow in Everfrost is one of the main reasons I made a barb shaman.  <i>Anything</i> to get rid of the frigging rain for a while is welcomed.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">AbMagFab</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The environment is also supposed to be changing in preparation for the Velious launch.  It's been said they are introducing a new ice age.  So expect to see it start to snow a lot more in areas like Greater Faydark!<P>AbMagFab<BR>52nd Elementalist<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
